    public interface ThrowableHandler<H,R>
    Represents an object which can properly handle a thrown throwable within itself. The throwing object call is wrapped within another object which handles a thrown throwable by the call.
    Since:
    1.0.0

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      R handle(H handler)
      Returns an object that handles the throwable thrown if this throwing object was unable to finish.
      R swallow()
      Returns an object that swallows the throwable thrown if this throwing object was unable to finish.

    • Method Detail

      • handle

        R handle(H handler)
        Returns an object that handles the throwable thrown if this throwing object was unable to finish.
        Parameters:
        handler - the object to handle if a throwable was thrown
        Returns:
        an object which handles any throwable thrown by this throwing object

      • swallow

        R swallow()
        Returns an object that swallows the throwable thrown if this throwing object was unable to finish. The value returned will be the default value as defined by section 4.12.5 of The Java Language Specification.
        Returns:
        an object which swallows any throwable thrown by this throwing object
        Java Language Specification:
        4.12.5 Initial Values of Variables
